expressionObject

public static final OWLObjectProperty expressionObject
This is not is not a standard part of OWL-S 1.1. It represents an alternative to expressionBody and is supposed to be used whenever the body of some expression should refer to some individual. Since it is declared as an object property it is not similar to expressionBody. The range of the latter are XML literals (no matter what this literal actually represents), whereas this property refers to some OWL individual.
